  "texts": [
    "This choice is based on our assumption that the \"Doppler waves\" related to both human-generated and ChatGPT-generated content propagate in a linear fashion, or to put it differently, we assume that the source's waveform moves along the line of the observer's sight.Firstly, we compute the unique values in an embedding of the text (V ( -→ x)), and then employ the Bessel function (J 0 (α n)) to determine a specific source frequency (E f0), which is then further utilized to compute E f. This is based on the idea that each human response vibrates at a distinct frequency.",
    "Furthermore, we employ explainable artificial intelligence (XAI) techniques, specifically Integrated Gradients (IG), to generate various perturbations of the input embedding.",
    "This is done to observe the behavior and outputs of different perturbed inputs from the perspective of an observer.",
    "We are motivated to understand how different perturbations of a particular input influence the perceived nature of the response.",
    "For instance, when a human rephrases a sentence using ChatGPT, the output should indicate that the response is generated by ChatGPT."
  ],
